John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1670166,"age":52,"year":"1682","julianDay":2335399,"title":"The Palace of Versailles","description":"The Palace of Versailles was originally known as a hunting log and retreat for Louis XII. When Louis XIV took over he moved his family into it. After he died the palace was abandoned. It has since been turned into a museum.","url":"https://www.britannica.com/topic/Palace-of-Versailles","urlTitle":"Encyclopedia Britannica- Palace of Versailles","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas GARAT was born in 1630, in La Broque, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France, his father, Nicolas GARAT, was 26 and his mother, Alizon N., was 21. He married Marguerite MICHEL on 18 February 1659, in Schirmeck, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 4 daughters. He died in 1699, in Schirmeck, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France, at the age of 69."},"et":{"1630–1699":"1630–1699","1630–1664":"1630–1664","1637–1687":"1637–1687","1620–Female":"1620–Surnud","1660–1690":"1660–1690","1661–1732":"1661–1732","1665–1736":"1665–1736","1670–1702":"1670–1702","–Female":"Surnud","1605–Male":"1605–Surnud","1610–Female":"1610–Surnud","environ 1661":"umbes 1661","environ 1660":"umbes 1660","1682":"1682","1660":"1660","1 janvier 1665":"1. jaanuar 1665","1 janvier 1687":"1. jaanuar 1687","18 février 1659":"18. veebruar 1659","1699":"1699","1732":"1732","1610":"1610","1630":"1630","1736":"1736","1637":"1637","avant 1690":"enne 1690","environ 1630":"umbes 1630","environ 1670":"umbes 1670","1670":"1670","1690":"1690","1665":"1665","1687":"1687","1620":"1620","1664":"1664","1661":"1661","1605":"1605","1702":"1702","La Broque, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"La Broque, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Pr